CP2K_INPUT
Section handling input for atomic calculations, for example
basis, pseudopotential, energy optimization. Doesn't look
like the thing which needs to be supported by AiiDA
Section to setup parameters for debug runs.
It's not a good idea to make debugs of cp2k
through AiiDA interface
Section for external restart, specifies an external input file
where to take all the restart parameters.
AiiDA definetly has to be able to automatically handle this
section
Testing cp2k is not AiiDA's buisness
Describes a basis optimization job, in which an
ADMM like approach is used to find the best
exponents and/or coefficients to match a given
training set.
I don't think that AiiDA has to set up this kind
of jobs. Or, another plugin can be created to
run atomic calculations.
Describes an input optimization job,
in which parameters in input files get optimized.
For example it can be used to fit force field parameters
to forces and energies obtained using DFT.
I would avoid to put this functionality into a standard
cp2k plugin, because philosophy of handling input and
output parameters is completely different from the one,
which you would use to study materials and their properties
with cp2k
This section defines a set of tool connected
with the motion of the nuclei.
Definetly has to be included into AiiDA, but
I don't think, that there should be some logic.
Describes a farming job, in which
multiple inputs are executed.
I think it would be better if AiiDA will take
care of running many jobs and distributing
resourses among them. If it correct, that this
section doesn't need to be present
Parameters needed to calculate energy and forces and describe
the system you want to analyze. This section has to be present
for sure. Some part of it can be generated automatically, like:
unit cell, coordinates, topology. Some of them have to be put
manually: DFT section
This section describes how to handle multiple force_evals.
Contains no sections, only two keywords. Can be put manually
Section with general information regarding which kind of simulation to
perform an parameters for the whole PROGRAM. Mostly contains
technical parameters : which library use, how much memory allocate,
etc. These things has to be generated automatically. The only important
keyword is RUN_TYPE which user has to specify
